@industry_expand_cec
subtitle: -1.5 Budget - Heavy Industry remains the core of the industrial sector, and we can restore it.
view-if: left_eco_adopted or both_eco_adopted
on-arrival: {!
Q.budget -= 1.5;
Q.central_industry_health += 2.3 * Q.bureaucratic_modifier;
!}

Though relatively untouched, the factories have remained fairly idle following the civil war, and we can stimulate investment into these factories to expand them and get them functioning once more.

@industry_expand_nep
subtitle: -1 Budget - We can subsidise small industries to stimulate them.
view-if: right_eco_adopted
on-arrival: {!
Q.budget -= 1;
Q.central_industry_health += 1.3 * Q.bureaucratic_modifier;
!}

Investments, especially foreign, have dried up since the civil war, leaving many smaller businesses unsustainable. Though against our goals, we could help to subsidise these businesses to stimulate the economy.

@supply_railways_expand
subtitle: -1 Budget - Railways are essential for our agricultural transports.
on-arrival: {!
Q.budget -= 1;
Q.central_supply_health += 2.5 * Q.bureaucratic_modifier;
!}

Railways, especially Freight Railways, remain scarce across the region. We can construct new railways with funding to restore connection between the regions, especially as their necessity furthers as time goes on.

@central_supply_repair
subtitle: -0.5 Budget - We can repair the remaining railways that still exist in the region.
on-arrival: {!
Q.budget -= 0.5;
Q.central_supply_health += 1.8;
!}
max-visits: 2

The railways, albeit damaged, still exist across the region. Some funding would allow for us to restore these infrastructure, being cheaper than building new railways without bureaucracy.

@central_supply_trade
subtitle: -1 Budget - The Centre Region acts as a Market between the Northern and Southern Regions.
view-if: both_eco_adopted
on-arrival: {!
Q.budget -= 1;
Q.central_supply_health += 1.4 * Q.bureaucratic_modifier;
Q.central_agricultural_health += 0.3 * Q.bureaucratic_modifier;
Q.central_industry_health += 0.3 * Q.bureaucratic_modifier;
!}
max-visits: 2

The Centre Region is where the difference in Regional Dualism blurs, as Central Planning and Open Markets meet. Thus, specific regions have been opened up to facilitate and mitigate conflict, as well as mediate in the event of conflict regardless. Expanding these regions will prove beneficial to us.

